misconceptions.inferred_category_name: No conceptual error (correct shift with wraparound)
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes they must save the last element, shift all elements right by copying from left to right (iterating backwards to avoid overwriting), then place the saved last element into index 0.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No gap: this matches Java’s array semantics and the correct in-place right-rotation-by-1 algorithm. Iterating from N-1 down to 1 correctly avoids overwriting values that are still needed.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: No error; produces correct output for N>0 and also safely handles N==0 by skipping the shift and printing an empty shifted line.
